description:
The appointee will report to the System Engineering Services Manager and is responsible for network infrastructure planning, implementation, administration monitoring and trouble shooting.  Your prerequisite attributes are:

University/Tertiary graduate in related disciplines;
At least 3 years’ experience in Windows Server and network configuration and administration;
In-depth network knowledge and solid hands-on experience in firewall, routers and switches;
Experience in VCP is an advantage.

We offer competitive remuneration plus comprehensive fringe benefits.  Interested parties, please send full resume and salary expected to Senior Human Resources Officer, Meyer Aluminium Ltd, 5 Dai Li Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Tai Po, New Territories.  or clicking "Apply Now'.  All applications will be treated in strictly confidential.

The Company
Our client is one of the largest Chinese Investment Banks in Hong Kong. Currently expanding their infrastructure team and looking for Server and Network support. 

The Role 

Handle daily operations on network and security;
Handle network and security equipment installation and configuration;
Handle troubleshooting, incident support, and coordination with service partner and carriers;
Provide onsite support for among HK office and remote support for CN offices;
Work closely with application and Helpdesk team to prepare applications and service roll-out;
Research on new information technology and perform product evaluation with vendors;
Handle and support user side scheduled and ad hoc requests;
Assist in suggesting and implementing improvement solution on daily internal and user operations;
Other IT related ad-hoc tasks when needed. 

Your Profile


Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines;
IT certification holder such as CCNA, CCNP or equivalent is preferable;
Minimum 5 years practical experience in IT infrastructure. Candidate with less experience will also be considered as junior role;
Solid Hands-on experience in Cisco router and switch; reputable firewall (e.g. CheckPoint, Fortigate, Palo Alto etc.), WIFI etc.;
Knowledge of VLANs, routing, switching, IPSec VPN, and IPv4/IPv6 addressing;
Experience of administrate security related systems and related products such as IDS, IPS, WAF, EDR, UEBA, SIEM and NAC etc is added advantage;
Experience of build and maintain data center for Financial Services with Cloud Services like AliCloud, Huawei Cloud, AWS etc is added advantage;
Experience in using issue tracking systems, network monitoring system is added advantage;
Exposure to different IT infrastructure and vendor products;
Good analytical mind, problem solving and communication skills;
Team player, responsible, independent, self-starter, motivated, multitasking and able to take initiative to get projects completed;
Good spoken and writing in Mandarin; knowledge of Cantonese/English is a plus. 

Apply Today
To apply online (Word attachment only), please click the 'Apply' button. Interested parties please apply with the most updated CV with expected salary and available date via JobsDB. Applicants who do not hear from us within 2 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. 

About Pathos
We are Pathos Consultancy Limited, a boutique recruitment firm based in Hong Kong strategically placing our candidates across all levels in permanent, temporary and contract roles.  We specialize in IT and finance roles for banking, financial services and listed MNC sectors.

Responsibilities:
 

Work in the IT Infrastructure team;

Handle the daily operation on network and security;

Handle network and security equipment installation and configuration;

Handle troubleshooting, incident support, and coordination with service partner and carriers;

Hand on experience of maintains connectivity among HK and CN offices.

Work closely with application and Helpdesk team to prepare applications and service roll-out;

Research on new information technology and perform product evaluation with vendors;

Handle and support user side scheduled and ad hoc requests;

Assist in suggesting and implementing improvement solution on daily internal and user operations;

Other IT related ad-hoc tasks when needed.
   

Requirements:
  
 

Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines;

Minimum 3 years practical experience in IT infrastructure. Candidate with less experience will also be considered as junior role;

Solid Hands-on experience in Cisco router and switch; reputable firewall (e.g. CheckPoint, Fortigate, Palo Alto etc.), WIFI etc.;

Experience of administrate security related systems and related products such as IDS, IPS, WAF, EDR, UEBA, SIEM, NAC, PAM, anti-virus and APT solution, and Sandbox solution, etc.;

Experience of build and maintain data center for Financial Services with Cloud Services like AliCloud, Huawei Cloud, AWS etc.;

Knowledge of VLANs, routing, switching, IPSec VPN, and IPv4/IPv6 addressing;

IT certification holder such as CCNA, CCNP or equivalent is preferable;

Experience in using issue tracking systems, network monitoring system is added advantage;

Working experience in FSI sector is an added advantage;

Exposure to different IT infrastructure and vendor products;

Required to work overtime for non-office hour deployment or support;

Good analytical mind, problem solving and communication skills;

Team player, responsible, independent, self-starter, motivated, multitasking and able to take initiative to get projects completed;

                     Good spoken and writing in Mandarin; knowledge of Cantonese/English is a plus.

 Application:

We offer an attractive remuneration package including a performance bonus, medical insurance covering dependents, MPF, Life and AD&D insurance, annual leave, birthday leave, marriage leave and training subsidy, etc. to the right candidate. 

If you are interested in this opportunity, please send your application with a detailed resume including current and expected salary, latest bonus and availability by clicking "Apply Now". Applications without required information will NOT be considered.

*Information provided by applicants will be treated in the strictest confidence and will be solely used for recruitment purpose

Assistant Information Security Manager / Senior Information Security Officer – Information Technology Services Centre (Ref: AISM / SISO (ITSC) 2022-01-14)

(Ref: AISM / SISO (ITSC) 2022-01-14)



Responsibilities:

review and update security documents such as policies and guidelines;
assess risks on applications, systems, networks and adopt security measures in a balance manner for risk mitigation;
audit and run tests on systems and infrastructure to identity possible issues;
ensure digital assets adequately protected, effectively monitored and managed;
provide latest updates on information security to general users to increase their awareness; and
explore suitable information security technologies that can better safeguard the information in the university.

Applicants should:

possess a recognised bachelor’s degree or above in Computer Science or related discipline;
possess updated and relevant qualifications such as CISM, CISSP, CEH, ISO27001;
preferably have at least 10 years of relevant work experience;
have proven records in information security and system auditing in application, networks and system level;
have good interpersonal, communication, analytical and problem-solving skills;
have good command of written and spoken English and Chinese; and
be pleasant with positive mindset, good customer sense and willing to learn new technologies.

The appointee will be required to work during non-office hours.  Work experience in the higher education sector will be an advantage.  Applicants with fewer years of experience could be considered as Senior Information Security Officer. 


Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested applicant should visit this link https://recruit.hsu.edu.hk/ and apply on or before 30 January 2022.  The University reserves the right not to fill the position in this exercise.

Applicants who are not invited to an interview within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful.  All information received will be treated in strict confidence, and the data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  The Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request.

the Hang Seng University of Hong Kong, incorporated in Hong Kong with limited liability by guarantee, is an equal opportunity employer.

The Challenge to You:


Introduce Cloud beauty and assist client toward Hybrid/Multi-Cloud transformation;
Study of major Cloud providers (Azure, AWS, Google Cloud, Alibaba Cloud… ) and present the latest cloud solutions from IaaS to SaaS to client and identify sales leads; 
Enable Sales team and other parties for Cloud offerings to drive Cloud development; 
Solution design, planning, and implement together with service engineer and project manager in different industries and scales; 
Provide consultation services, POC, and professional services for Cloud business.

Requirements:


Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related disciplines; 

Knowledge of any Cloud platform with experience in major areas like compute, storage, backup & recovery, etc.; 
Strong learner for exam and possession of existing Cloud certificate is an advantage; 
Good presentation and interpersonal skills; 
Self-motivated, strong analytical reasoning and problem solving skills; 
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese; 
Fresh graduates will also be considered

We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate.  Including on-job training, 5 days work week, medical insurance, performance incentive, etc.

For more information about Synnex, please visit http://www.synnex.com.hk

All information will be treated in strict confidence and will be used exclusively for recruitment related purpose only.
